@startuml
title Iteration 4 Timing Diagram (Main.TIME_SCALE = 20, real milliseconds)

note top
  Each time block below is a separate example run.
  Time markers are real milliseconds based on Main.TIME_SCALE = 20.
  Scheduler.run() uses wait(200).
  DroneExecutionEngine uses TICK_MS = 100, SOFT_RESET_SECONDS = 6.0,
  and PACKET_RETRY_SECONDS = 2.0.
end note

robust "Fire_Subsystem" as Fire
robust "Scheduler" as Scheduler
robust "Drone_1" as D1

@0
Fire is RUNNING
Scheduler is IDLE
D1 is IDLE

Fire@0 <-> @700 : Scenario 1\nStuck Mid-Flight
Scheduler@0 <-> @100 : putRequest(req) calls notifyAll()\nand wakes Scheduler.run() from wait(200)
D1@0 <-> @100 : commandLock.wait(COMMAND_WAIT_MS)\nwhile no DispatchCommand is ready

@100
Fire is TIMED_WAITING
Scheduler is DISPATCHING
D1 is EN_ROUTE

Scheduler@100 <-> @200 : assignMission() queues DispatchCommand\nand calls notifyAll()
D1@100 <-> @300 : injected fault delay = 4.0 simulated sec\nscaled to 200 ms real

@200
Scheduler is WAITING_FOR_DRONE

@300
Scheduler is WAITING_FOR_DRONE
D1 is RESETTING

D1@300 <-> @600 : timedStateWait(waitMs)\nsoft reset = 6.0 simulated sec\nscaled to 300 ms real
Scheduler@300 <-> @600 : soft fault received;\nmission stays active,\nno requeue

@600
Scheduler is WAITING_FOR_DRONE
D1 is EN_ROUTE

@700
Scheduler is WAITING_FOR_DRONE
D1 is DROPPING_AGENT

@800
Fire is RUNNING
Scheduler is IDLE
D1 is IDLE

Fire@800 <-> @1400 : Scenario 2\nNozzle Jammed
Scheduler@800 <-> @900 : putRequest(req) calls notifyAll()\nand wakes Scheduler.run() from wait(200)

@900
Fire is TIMED_WAITING
Scheduler is DISPATCHING
D1 is EN_ROUTE

Scheduler@900 <-> @1000 : assignMission() queues DispatchCommand\nand calls notifyAll()
D1@900 <-> @1200 : injected hard fault delay = 6.0 simulated sec\nscaled to 300 ms real

@1000
Scheduler is WAITING_FOR_DRONE
D1 is DROPPING_AGENT

@1200
Scheduler is DISPATCHING
D1 is OFFLINE

Scheduler@1200 <-> @1300 : handleHardFault(...)\nmissionQueue.addFirst(mission)\nnotifyAll() after requeue / next dispatch
D1@1200 <-> @1400 : hard fault latched;\nDrone_1 stays OFFLINE for this run

@1300
Scheduler is WAITING_FOR_DRONE
D1 is OFFLINE

@1500
Fire is RUNNING
Scheduler is IDLE
D1 is IDLE

Fire@1500 <-> @1900 : Scenario 3\nPacket Loss
Scheduler@1500 <-> @1600 : putRequest(req) calls notifyAll()\nand wakes Scheduler.run() from wait(200)

@1600
Fire is TIMED_WAITING
Scheduler is DISPATCHING
D1 is EN_ROUTE

Scheduler@1600 <-> @1700 : assignMission() queues DispatchCommand\nand calls notifyAll()
D1@1600 <-> @1700 : injected packet-loss delay = 2.0 simulated sec\nscaled to 100 ms real

@1700
Scheduler is WAITING_FOR_DRONE
D1 is EN_ROUTE

D1@1700 <-> @1800 : timedStateWait(scaledMillisForSimulationSeconds(2.0))\nretry timeout = 100 ms real
Scheduler@1700 <-> @1800 : first STATUS reports PACKET_LOSS;\nsecond STATUS is the retry;\nmission is not requeued

@1800
Scheduler is WAITING_FOR_DRONE
D1 is EN_ROUTE

@1900
Fire is TIMED_WAITING
Scheduler is WAITING_FOR_DRONE
D1 is EN_ROUTE

@enduml
